                <html:p>A relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:em><html:strong>equivalence relation</html:strong></html:em> when it is <fr:link href="/jms-00JX/" title="Preorder" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JX/" display-uri="jms-00JX" type="local">reflexive, transitive</fr:link>, and symmetric:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \forall  x\in  A\mathpunct {.} x\mathrel {E}x
]]></fr:tex>
