                <fr:title text="Set partition">Set partition</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>partition</html:strong></html:em> of a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P\subseteq  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> of non-empty subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> whose elements are referred to as <html:em><html:strong>blocks</html:strong></html:em>, satisfying the following conditions:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>the union of all blocks is all of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup  P = A]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
 <html:li>the blocks are pairwise disjoint, i.e. for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b_1\not = b_2\in  P]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b_1\cap  b_2 = \varnothing ]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
                <html:p>We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Part}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of partitions of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
